the feds to collect taxes! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 491<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/28/02 9:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=512.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/zilla.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Can't We Just Stop Getting Along?</span><hr size=1> Exactly.  There's no impetus for governments to develop human access to space except for their little elite astronaut corps.  People are very excited about China getting into the fray but I think we can agree that China, like other governments, would hesitate to create any kind of situation where people could migrate into space and possibly revolt.  It's just going to be more of the same &quot;lets send two or three people into space and wave our flags with nationalistic fervor.&quot;  Screw that kind of thinking.  The private sector and not just for-profit corporations, are our last resort to getting the ball rolling on access for the rest of us.  I want to grab my pickaxe and go mine an asteroid for platinum right now!  I think it'll be a good sign when we have to hide from the spacefaring version of the Rainbow Warrior as it protects the asteroids from scum humans.  We will certainly have arrived then.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A> at: 11/28/02 9:45:18 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=discovery1@nuclearspace>Discovery 1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/28/02 9:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=512.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/zilla.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Can't We Just Stop Getting Along?</span><hr size=1> Wait, there's something I don't understand. Even if a nation aggressively pursued an idea like Orion or Mauk2's Liberty Ship, it would take many decades for a significant population to inhabit space. I don't think any government would have to worry about space colonists to revolt, there would simply be too few to govern an independent state, I think.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaphod4468>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1564<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/28/02 10:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=512.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/user/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Can't We Just Stop Getting Along?</span><hr size=1> Eventually it would happen... Old World meets New World once again.<br>
